{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "bitcoin-watch-e2e",
    "name": "Bitcoin \u2013 Watch (POST /api/v1/bitcoin/watch)",
    "description": "E2E tests for POST /api/v1/bitcoin/watch.\n\nFolder execution order:\n  1. setup          \u2014 register a fresh user, fetch OTP from Gmail, verify email, login\n  2. unauthenticated \u2014 request without JWT \u2192 401\n  3. validation     \u2014 input-error cases (malformed JSON, network mismatch, address guards)\n  4. happy-path     \u2014 200 with single address, multiple addresses, re-registration (idempotent)\n  5. rate-limiting  \u2014 IP limiter exhaustion: 10 warmup \u2192 ok, 11th \u2192 429\n\nPre-requisites:\n  - BTC_NETWORK=testnet4 in .env (collection variable btc_network must match).\n  - Run `make _e2e-kv-clean` before each run to reset Redis watch state so the\n    per-user count cap and 7-day window are fresh.\n  - Run `make _e2e-db-clean` to remove the setup user between runs.\n\nNotes on what is NOT covered here (already covered by internal tests):\n  - HMAC of invalid address in audit metadata         \u2014 handler_test.go\n  - Redis unavailable \u2192 503 + Retry-After: 5          \u2014 handler_test.go (requires Redis down)\n  - watch_limit_exceeded reason=count_cap             \u2014 requires seeding user near limit in Redis;\n                                                        add a Makefile seed target to cover this.\n  - watch_limit_exceeded reason=registration_window_expired \u2014 requires seeding expired regAt key;\n                                                        add a Makefile seed target to cover this.\n  - addedCount==0 skips side-effects (no audit write) \u2014 service_test.go\n  - reconciliation goroutine correctness              \u2014 service_test.go\n  - All audit event writes                            \u2014 store_test.go\n\nAddresses used in happy-path are testnet4 standard test vectors:\n  - tb1qw508d6qejxtdg4y5r3zarvary0c5xw7kxpjzsx  (P2WPKH, BIP173 test vector)\n  - mipcBbFg9gMiCh81Kj8tqqdgoZub1ZJRfn           (P2PKH legacy testnet)\nIf running against mainnet, replace collection variable btc_network and swap\nthese addresses for mainnet equivalents.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Increment the request sequence counter and derive a unique X-Forwarded-For IP",
          "// for every request so non-RL folders never exhaust any rate-limit bucket.",
          "// The rate-limiting folder overrides _xff to 127.0.0.2 via its own prerequest.",
          "// Requires TRUSTED_PROXIES=127.0.0.1/32 in .env.",
          "const n = (pm.collectionVariables.get('_req_seq') | 0) + 1;",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_req_seq', n);",
          "const ip = '10.' + ((n>>16)&0xff) + '.' + ((n>>8)&0xff) + '.' + (n&0xff);",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_xff', ip);"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "setup",
      "description": "Registers the gmail_test_email user, fetches the OTP from Gmail, verifies the email, then logs in to obtain watch_access_token. The validation and happy-path folders depend on watch_access_token being set here.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /register \u2192 201 (setup user)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const email = pm.environment.get('gmail_test_email');",
                  "if (!email) {",
                  "    console.error('[ERROR] gmail_test_email not set in environment \u2014 add it to environment.json.');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('watch_happy_email', email);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('watch_happy_password', 'P@ssw0rd1!');"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('message field present and non-empty', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "",
                  "const token = pm.variables.get('gmail_access_token');",
                  "if (!token) { console.warn('[WARN] gmail_access_token not set \u2014 skipping Gmail fetch'); return; }",
                  "",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Waiting 8 s for verification email to arrive in Gmail...');",
                  "const start = Date.now();",
                  "while (Date.now() - start < 8000) {}",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Done waiting. Querying Gmail API (async)...');",
                  "",
                  "const query = encodeURIComponent('subject:\"Verify your\" newer_than:1h');",
                  "pm.sendRequest({",
                  "    url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages?q=' + query + '&maxResults=3',",
                  "    method: 'GET',",
                  "    header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token }",
                  "}, (err, res) => {",
                  "    if (err) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail list failed:', err); return; }",
                  "    if (res.code === 401) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail token expired'); return; }",
                  "    const msgs = res.json().messages;",
                  "    if (!msgs || !msgs.length) { console.warn('[WARN] No matching email found in Gmail.'); return; }",
                  "    pm.sendRequest({",
                  "        url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages/' + msgs[0].id + '?format=full',",
                  "        method: 'GET',",
                  "        header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token }",
                  "    }, (err2, res2) => {",
                  "        if (err2) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail fetch failed:', err2); return; }",
                  "        const msg = res2.json();",
                  "        let body = '';",
                  "        const parts = msg.payload && msg.payload.parts;",
                  "        if (parts && parts.length) {",
                  "            const p = parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/plain') || parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/html');",
                  "            if (p && p.body && p.body.data) body = atob(p.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/'));",
                  "        } else if (msg.payload && msg.payload.body && msg.payload.body.data) {",
                  "            body = atob(msg.payload.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/'));",
                  "        }",
                  "        if (!body) { console.warn('[WARN] Could not decode email body.'); return; }",
                  "        const match = body.match(/(?<!#)\\b(\\d{6})\\b/);",
                  "        if (!match) { console.warn('[WARN] No 6-digit OTP found in email body.'); return; }",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('watch_code', match[1]);",
                  "        console.log('[INFO] OTP stored in watch_code:', match[1]);",
                  "    });",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"display_name\": \"WatchHappy\", \"email\": \"{{watch_happy_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{watch_happy_password}}\"}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /verification \u2192 200 (consume OTP)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const code = pm.collectionVariables.get('watch_code');",
                  "if (!code) {",
                  "    console.error('[ERROR] watch_code is empty \u2014 Gmail fetch did not complete.');",
                  "    console.error('        Check: gmail_access_token is set and not expired, --delay-request >= 8000.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('message includes \"verified\"', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.include('verified'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"email\": \"{{watch_happy_email}}\", \"code\": \"{{watch_code}}\"}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/verification",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "verification"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /login \u2192 200 (obtain watch_access_token)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('access_token present and non-empty', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('access_token');",
                  "    pm.expect(body.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('watch_access_token', body.access_token);",
                  "console.log('[INFO] watch_access_token stored.');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"{{watch_happy_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{watch_happy_password}}\"}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
